    \\\"name\\\": \\\"Python\\\",\\n        \\\"level\\\": \\\"Expert\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"Machine Learning\\\",\\n        \\\"level\\\": \\\"Expert\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"Data Analysis\\\",\\n        \\\"level\\\": \\\"Proficient\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"SQL\\\",\\n        \\\"level\\\": \\\"Proficient\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"Deep Learning\\\",\\n        \\\"level\\\": \\\"Intermediate\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"Cloud Computing (AWS)\\\",\\n        \\\"level\\\": \\\"Intermediate\\\"\\n      }\\n    ],\\n    \\\"experience\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"position\\\": \\\"Data Scientist\\\",\\n        \\\"company\\\": \\\"Acme Corp\\\",\\n        \\\"start_date\\\": \\\"2020-06-01\\\",\\n        \\\"end_date\\\": \\\"2023-08-15\\\",\\n        \\\"responsibilities\\\": [\\n          \\\"Developed and deployed machine learning models for fraud detection, resulting in a 20% reduction in fraudulent transactions.\\\",\\n          \\\"Conducted data analysis to identify key business insights and trends.\\\",\\n          \\\"Collaborated with cross-functional teams to implement data-driven solutions.\\\",\\n          \\\"Built data pipelines for efficient data processing and storage.\\\"\\n        ]\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"position\\\": \\\"Data Analyst\\\",\\n        \\\"company\\\": \\\"Beta Inc.\\\",\\n        \\\"start_date\\\": \\\"2019-01-02\\\",\\n        \\\"end_date\\\": \\\"2020-05-31\\\",\\n        \\\"responsibilities\\\": [\\n          \\\"Performed data analysis to support business decision-making.\\\",\\n          \\\"Created dashboards and reports to visualize key performance indicators.\\\",\\n          \\\"Assisted in the development of machine learning models.\\\"\\n        ]\\n      }\\n    ],\\n    \\\"education\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"degree\\\": \\\"M.Sc. Data Science\\\",\\n        \\\"institution\\\": \\\"University of California, Berkeley\\\",\\n        \\\"start_year\\\": 2017,\\n        \\\"end_year\\\": 2018,\\n        \\\"grade\\\": \\\"3.9/4.0\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"degree\\\": \\\"B.Sc. Statistics\\\",\\n        \\\"institution\\\": \\\"University of Michigan\\\",\\n        \\\"start_year\\\": 2013,\\n        \\\"end_year\\\": \\\"2016\\\",\\n        \\\"grade\\\": \\\"3.7/4.0\\\"\\n      }\\n    ],\\n    \\\"projects\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"Customer Churn Prediction\\\",\\n        \\\"description\\\": \\\"Developed a machine learning model to predict customer churn with 85% accuracy.\\\",\\n        \\\"skills\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"Machine Learning\\\", \\\"Data Analysis\\\"]\\n      }\\n    ],\\n    \\\"certifications\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"AWS Certified Machine Learning Specialist\\\",\\n        \\\"issuing_organization\\\": \\\"Amazon Web Services\\\",\\n        \\\"issue_date\\\": \\\"2022-12-01\\\"\\n      }\\n    ]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nTask task3:\\n  Objective: Build an email automation component to send interview invites and follow-ups triggered by interview module events.\\nTask task4:\\n  Objective: Create a scoring algorithm that evaluates candidate responses against expected answers and outputs scores in JSON.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nDevelop the technical interview module: generate questions based on job and resume JSON and capture candidate responses.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nJSON\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```txt\\n1. Analyze the job description using the JSON schema from task0 to understand the required skills, experience, and responsibilities.\\n2. Analyze the candidate's resume using the JSON schema from task1 to identify their skills, experience, and education.\\n3. Create a list of technical interview questions based on the job description's required skills and the candidate's resume. Prioritize questions that assess the candidate's proficiency in the required skills, especially those listed as \\\"expert\\\" or \\\"proficient\\\" in the resume.\\n4. Structure the interview questions to cover different aspects such as theoretical knowledge, practical application, and problem-solving abilities. Include questions that require the candidate to explain concepts, write code snippets, and debug existing code.\\n5. Send an email to the candidate with the interview schedule and instructions (using task3).\\n6. Conduct the technical interview, asking the prepared questions and recording the candidate's responses. Ensure to note the time taken for each response and any clarifications needed.\\n7. Score each candidate's response using the scoring algorithm from task4, considering the accuracy, completeness, and clarity of the answer.\\n8. Generate a final evaluation report that includes the candidate's scores for each question, an overall score, and a summary of their strengths and weaknesses.\\n9. Store the interview data, candidate responses, scores, and evaluation report in a structured format (e.g., JSON).\\n10. Send a follow-up email to the candidate with the interview results (using task3).\\n```\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-28T12:25:41.981016\"\n}"}
