rioritize questions that assess the candidate's proficiency in the required skills, especially those listed as \\\"expert\\\" or \\\"proficient\\\" in the resume.\\n4. Structure the interview questions to cover different aspects such as theoretical knowledge, practical application, and problem-solving abilities. Include questions that require the candidate to explain concepts, write code snippets, and debug existing code.\\n5. Send an email to the candidate with the interview schedule and instructions (using task3).\\n6. Conduct the technical interview, asking the prepared questions and recording the candidate's responses. Ensure to note the time taken for each response and any clarifications needed.\\n7. Score each candidate's response using the scoring algorithm from task4, considering the accuracy, completeness, and clarity of the answer.\\n8. Generate a final evaluation report that includes the candidate's scores for each question, an overall score, and a summary of their strengths and weaknesses.\\n9. Store the interview data, candidate responses, scores, and evaluation report in a structured format (e.g., JSON).\\n10. Send a follow-up email to the candidate with the interview results (using task3).\\n```\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"role\": \"assistant\",\n      \"content\": \"---\\n## FEEDBACK to VERSION 0\\nhere are some feedbacks:\\n- The output is in plain text steps rather than the required JSON format.\\n- It does not actually generate interview questions or placeholders for capturing candidate responses.\\n- It lacks structure for linking questions to skills, tracking response times, and storing responses.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"interviewModule\\\": {\\n    \\\"jobDescriptionId\\\": \\\"JOB12345\\\",\\n    \\\"candidateId\\\": \\\"CAND67890\\\",\\n    \\\"questions\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"questionId\\\": \\\"Q1\\\",\\n        \\\"skill\\\": \\\"JavaScript\\\",\\n        \\\"level\\\": \\\"expert\\\",\\n        \\\"type\\\":