{"timestamp": "2026-05-28 12:26:21,970", "level": "INFO", "logger": "flow.validation", "module": "logging_config", "function": "log_validation_result", "line": 185, "message": "{\"timestamp\": \"2026-05-28T12:26:21.970168\", \"task_id\": \"unknown\", \"task_objective\": \"Create a scoring algorithm that evaluates candidate responses against expected answers and outputs scores in JSON.\", \"result\": \"```txt\\n1. Analyze the job description.\\n2. Analyze the candidate resume.\\n3. Generate technical interview questions based on job description and resume.\\n4. Send interview invitation email to candidate.\\n5. Conduct technical interview.\\n6. Capture candidate responses to each question.\\n7. Score candidate responses against expected answers.\\n8. Send follow-up email to candidate.\\n9. Generate final evaluation report.\\n```\", \"validation_type\": \"text\", \"status\": \"completed\", \"feedback\": \"here are some feedbacks:\\n- The result provided is just a list of steps and does not include a scoring algorithm or JSON output as required.\\n- You need to specify how candidate responses are compared to expected answers, how scores are calculated, and present the output in JSON format.\\n\\nhere are the changes:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"scoringAlgorithm\\\": {\\n    \\\"description\\\": \\\"Compare candidate responses to expected answers using keyword overlap and phrase similarity. Assign a score between 0 and maxScore for each question.\\\",\\n    \\\"parameters\\\": {\\n      \\\"maxScorePerQuestion\\\": 10,\\n      \\\"keywordWeight\\\": 0.7,\\n      \\\"similarityWeight\\\": 0.3\\n    },\\n    \\\"steps\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"step\\\": 1,\\n        \\\"action\\\": \\\"Tokenize expected and candidate answers, normalize case, remove stop words.\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"step\\\": 2,\\n        \\\"action\\\": \\\"Count keywordMatches = number of expected-answer keywords found in candidateAnswer.\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"step\\\": 3,\\n        \\\"action\\\": \\\"Compute keywordScore = (keywordMatches / totalExpectedKeywords) * maxScorePerQuestion * keywordWeight.\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"step\\\": 4,\\n        \\\"action\\\": \\\"Compute semanticSimilarityScore via a simple string similarity metric (e.g., Jaccard index or edit distance) scaled to maxScorePerQuestion * similarityWeight.\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"step\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"action\\\": \\\"TotalScore = round(keywordScore + semanticSimilarityScore, 2).\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"step\\\": 6,\\n        \\\"action\\\": \\\"Ensure TotalScore does not exceed maxScorePerQuestion or drop below 0.\\\"\\n      }\\n    ]\\n  },\\n  \\\"evaluateResponses\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"questionId\\\": \\\"Q1\\\",\\n      \\\"expectedAnswer\\\": \\\"Use a hash map to store counts and iterate over the array once, achieving O(n) time complexity.\\\",\\n      \\\"candidateAnswer\\\": \\\"I would use a dictionary to count occurrences in one pass, so it runs in linear time.\\\",\\n      \\\"scoring\\\": {\\n        \\\"keywordMatches\\\": 3,\\n        \\\"totalExpectedKeywords\\\": 5,\\n        \\\"keywordScore\\\": 4.2,\\n        \\\"semanticSimilarityScore\\\": 2.8,\\n        \\\"totalScore\\\": 7.0,\\n        \\\"maxScore\\\": 10\\n      }\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"questionId\\\": \\\"Q2\\\",\\n      \\\"expectedAnswer\\\": \\\"Implement binary search on the sorted list, which has a time complexity of O(log n).\\\",\\n      \\\"candidateAnswer\\\": \\\"I’d sort the list and then do binary search to find the element quickly with logarithmic time.\\\",\\n      \\\"scoring\\\": {\\n        \\\"keywordMatches\\\": 4,\\n        \\\"totalExpectedKeywords\\\": 6,\\n        \\\"keywordScore\\\": 4.67,\\n        \\\"semanticSimilarityScore\\\": 2.33,\\n        \\\"totalScore\\\": 7.0,\\n        \\\"maxScore\\\": 10\\n      }\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\"}"}
