    \\\"name\\\": \\\"Python\\\",\\n        \\\"level\\\": \\\"Expert\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"Machine Learning\\\",\\n        \\\"level\\\": \\\"Expert\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"Data Analysis\\\",\\n        \\\"level\\\": \\\"Proficient\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"SQL\\\",\\n        \\\"level\\\": \\\"Proficient\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"Deep Learning\\\",\\n        \\\"level\\\": \\\"Intermediate\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"Cloud Computing (AWS)\\\",\\n        \\\"level\\\": \\\"Intermediate\\\"\\n      }\\n    ],\\n    \\\"experience\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"position\\\": \\\"Data Scientist\\\",\\n        \\\"company\\\": \\\"Acme Corp\\\",\\n        \\\"start_date\\\": \\\"2020-06-01\\\",\\n        \\\"end_date\\\": \\\"2023-08-15\\\",\\n        \\\"responsibilities\\\": [\\n          \\\"Developed and deployed machine learning models for fraud detection, resulting in a 20% reduction in fraudulent transactions.\\\",\\n          \\\"Conducted data analysis to identify key business insights and trends.\\\",\\n          \\\"Collaborated with cross-functional teams to implement data-driven solutions.\\\",\\n          \\\"Built data pipelines for efficient data processing and storage.\\\"\\n        ]\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"position\\\": \\\"Data Analyst\\\",\\n        \\\"company\\\": \\\"Beta Inc.\\\",\\n        \\\"start_date\\\": \\\"2019-01-02\\\",\\n        \\\"end_date\\\": \\\"2020-05-31\\\",\\n        \\\"responsibilities\\\": [\\n          \\\"Performed data analysis to support business decision-making.\\\",\\n          \\\"Created dashboards and reports to visualize key performance indicators.\\\",\\n          \\\"Assisted in the development of machine learning models.\\\"\\n        ]\\n      }\\n    ],\\n    \\\"education\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"degree\\\": \\\"M.Sc. Data Science\\\",\\n        \\\"institution\\\": \\\"University of California, Berkeley\\\",\\n        \\\"start_year\\\": 2017,\\n        \\\"end_year\\\": 2018,\\n        \\\"grade\\\": \\\"3.9/4.0\\\"\\n      },\\n      {\\n        \\\"degree\\\": \\\"B.Sc. Statistics\\\",\\n        \\\"institution\\\": \\\"University of Michigan\\\",\\n        \\\"start_year\\\": 2013,\\n        \\\"end_year\\\": \\\"2016\\\",\\n        \\\"grade\\\": \\\"3.7/4.0\\\"\\n      }\\n    ],\\n    \\\"projects\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"Customer Churn Prediction\\\",\\n        \\\"description\\\": \\\"Developed a machine learning model to predict customer churn with 85% accuracy.\\\",\\n        \\\"skills\\\": [\\\"Python\\\", \\\"Machine Learning\\\", \\\"Data Analysis\\\"]\\n      }\\n    ],\\n    \\\"certifications\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"AWS Certified Machine Learning Specialist\\\",\\n        \\\"issuing_organization\\\": \\\"Amazon Web Services\\\",\\n        \\\"issue_date\\\": \\\"2022-12-01\\\"\\n      }\\n    ]\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\nTask task4:\\n  Objective: Create a scoring algorithm that evaluates candidate responses against expected answers and outputs scores in JSON.\\n  Result: ```txt\\n1. Analyze the job description.\\n2. Analyze the candidate resume.\\n3. Generate technical interview questions based on job description and resume.\\n4. Send interview invitation email to candidate.\\n5. Conduct technical interview.\\n6. Capture candidate responses to each question.\\n7. Score candidate responses against expected answers.\\n8. Send follow-up email to candidate.\\n9. Generate final evaluation report.\\n```\\n\\n---\\n# **Downstream Tasks Objectives**\\nNo downstream objectives available.\\n\\n---\\n# **Current Task Requirements**\\nImplement a report generator that compiles job requirements, candidate profile, interview responses, and scores into a .txt evaluation report.\\n\\n---\\n\\n# **Required Output Format**\\nPlain text\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"gpt_response\": \"```text\\n1. Analyze the job description using the job description parser (task0) to extract required skills, experience, and responsibilities.\\n2. Analyze the candidate's resume using the resume parser (task1) to extract skills, experience, education, and projects.\\n3. Conduct a technical interview, potentially using questions generated in task4.\\n4. Capture candidate responses during the interview.\\n5. Score candidate responses using the scoring algorithm (task4).\\n6. Compile the job requirements (from step 1), candidate profile (from step 2), interview responses (from step 4), and scores (from step 5) into a final evaluation report.\\n7. Save the final evaluation report as a .txt file.\\n```\\n\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-28T12:26:24.281895\"\n}"}
