kills and data structures & algorithms fundamentals.\\n- Excellent communication and teamwork abilities.\\n\\n2. CANDIDATE PROFILE\\n--------------------\\nName: John Doe\\nExperience: 4 years\\nEducation: B.S. in Computer Science, University X, 2019\\nTechnical Skills:\\n  - Languages: Python (4 yrs), Java (3 yrs), JavaScript (2 yrs)\\n  - Frameworks: Spring Boot, Flask, React\\n  - Databases: PostgreSQL, MongoDB\\n  - Tools: Git, Docker, Jenkins\\nProjects:\\n  - Inventory Management System (Python, Flask, PostgreSQL)\\n  - E-commerce Platform (Java, Spring Boot, MongoDB)\\nCertifications:\\n  - AWS Certified Solutions Architect – Associate\\n\\n3. INTERVIEW QUESTIONS & RESPONSES\\n---------------------------------\\nQ1. Explain how you would design a RESTful API for managing user profiles.\\nA1. “I would define resources as /users and support CRUD via HTTP methods. For URL versioning, I’d use /v1/users. I’d implement pagination for list endpoints, validation using JSON Schema, and secure endpoints with OAuth 2.0. Error handling would follow HTTP status codes, e.g., 404 for not found.”\\n  \\nQ2. Describe how you optimize a slow database query.\\nA2. “First, I’d examine the query execution plan to identify bottlenecks. Then I’d add appropriate indexes, rewrite joins to reduce nested loops, and consider denormalization or materialized views for heavy aggregation. I’d also monitor database metrics to ensure improvements.”\\n\\nQ3. Solve this algorithm problem: Given an array of integers, find the subarray with maximum sum (Kadane’s algorithm).\\nA3. “Initialize max_current and max_global to the first element. Iterate from the second element: max_current = max(element, max_current + element); if max_current > max_global, update max_global. This runs in O(n) time and O(1) space.”\\n\\n4. SCORES\\n---------\\nScoring Scale: 1 (Poor) – 5 (Excellent)\\n\\nQuestion 1: API Design  \\n  - Criteria: completeness, security, error handling  \\n  - Score: 5 / 5\\n\\nQuestion 2: Database Optimization  \\n  - Criteria: approach clarity, tools, practical considerations  \\n  - Score: 4 / 5\\n\\nQuestion 3: Algorithm & Problem Solving  \\n  - Criteria: correctness, efficiency, explanation  \\n  - Score: 5 / 5\\n\\nOverall Score: (5 + 4 + 5) / 3 = 4.67\\n\\n5. SUMMARY & RECOMMENDATION\\n---------------------------\\nJohn Doe demonstrates strong technical knowledge in API design, database optimization, and algorithms. His communication is clear, and he provided structured, efficient solutions. With 4 years of relevant experience and solid credentials, he meets and exceeds the position requirements.\\n\\nRecommendation: Strongly recommend extending an offer for the Software Engineer position.\\n\\n------------------------------------------------------------\\nEnd of Report\\n------------------------------------------------------------\"}"}
